# Code owners for open-bridge.
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the listed owner(s) on any pull request
# that touches a matching path. Combined with branch protection on `main`
# (required pull-request review), this means nothing merges without a
# maintainer's approval — the floor for the manual-then-AI-assisted merge
# process described in the project's contribution workflow.
#
# Two maintainers co-own the default paths, so either can give the required
# code-owner approval on the other's PR (no self-approval on GitHub). To move
# to team-based ownership later, replace the handles with a team such as
# @bks-lab/maintainers — CODEOWNERS lines accept teams and users alike.

# Default owners for the whole repository.
*                       @mboiman @avondiel-dev

# Extra-sensitive areas — deliberately lead-only, overriding `*` (last
# matching rule wins): legal/CI/leak-gate must always stay lead-reviewed.
/LICENSE                @mboiman
/TRADEMARK.md           @mboiman
/AUTHORS                @mboiman
/.github/               @mboiman
/scripts/               @mboiman
